yes. She asked where they were. He pointed right away . . . to hers!

messages.messageBody:
Julie (snort, snort, wiping tears from cheeks from so much laughter) that
was just about the best thing I have ever heard!! Thanks for making my day!

I can add to that list (although, my 2.5 yo dd also sing "i'm not stupid")

"Why are your mom's boob's so big?" (3yo friend says to Mira my nearly 5yo
dd)
" She probably has a lot of milk in them?" (Mira)
"Nope, I'm just wearing a padded, push-up bra." (me, 30 yo barely A cup,
certainly not lactating for over a year)

I have always thought big boobs are worth discussing, but when you've got to
wear a contraption to just SEEM like a B, I don't think they qualify as
"big".

Good luck with the goats!
DiAnna
